.TH CWD 1 "2026" "The-JLC-Project" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
cwd \- print the current working directory
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B cwd
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B cwd
prints the absolute path of the current working directory to standard output,
followed by a newline.
It uses
.BR getcwd (3)
with dynamic allocation so arbitrarily long paths are handled correctly.
This is the JLC equivalent of
.BR pwd (1).
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
.BR getcwd (3)
failed.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Print the current directory:
.B cwd
.TP
Capture in a variable:
.EX
HERE=$(cwd)
echo "Working in $HERE"
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR pwd (1),
.BR lf (1)
.SH AUTHORS
The-JLC-Project contributors.
